<i>adverb</i>: 조만간 [조ː만간], 이내 [이내], 쉬이 [쉬이], 쉬 [쉬ː], 속히 [소키], 금세 [금세], 금방 [금방], 곧 [곧] <i>noun</i>: 방금 [방금], 미구 [미ː구], 낼모레 [낼ː모레], 내일모레 [내일모레], 근간 [근ː간] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adverb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>조만간 [조ː만간]</dt><br>
<dd>soon</dd><br>
<dd>머지않아 곧.</dd><br>
<dd>Before long and in the foreseeable future.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>이내 [이내]</dt><br>
<dd>1. soon; promptly; in a moment</dd><br>
<dd>그때 곧. 또는 때를 늦추지 않고 바로.</dd><br>
<dd>Immediately at that moment; without delay.</dd><br>
<dd>2. ever since</dd><br>
<dd>어느 때부터 계속.</dd><br>
<dd>Continuously from a certain moment.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>쉬이 [쉬이]</dt><br>
<dd>1. easily; readily</dd><br>
<dd>힘들거나 어렵지 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>Without trouble or difficulty.</dd><br>
<dd>2. easily</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 일어날 가능성이 많게.</dd><br>
<dd>With a high possibility that something will happen.</dd><br>
<dd>3. soon; before long</dd><br>
<dd>금방이나 길지 않은 시간 후에.</dd><br>
<dd>Shortly or after a short time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>쉬 [쉬ː]</dt><br>
<dd>1. easily</dd><br>
<dd>힘들거나 어렵지 않게.</dd><br>
<dd>Without hardship or difficulty.</dd><br>
<dd>2. easily</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 일이 일어날 가능성이 많게.</dd><br>
<dd>With a lot of possibility of happening.</dd><br>
<dd>3. easily; soon</dd><br>
<dd>금방이나 길지 않은 시간 후에.</dd><br>
<dd>Shortly or in a little while.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>속히 [소키]</dt><br>
<dd>soon; quickly</dd><br>
<dd>서둘러서 꽤 빠르게.</dd><br>
<dd>Quite fast, in a hurry.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>금세 [금세]</dt><br>
<dd>immediately; soon</dd><br>
<dd>시간이 얼마 지나지 않아서.</dd><br>
<dd>Before long; shortly</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>금방 [금방]</dt><br>
<dd>1. moment ago</dd><br>
<dd>바로 얼마 전에.</dd><br>
<dd>A short time ago.</dd><br>
<dd>2. at any moment</dd><br>
<dd>지금이라도 당장.</dd><br>
<dd>At any minute now.</dd><br>
<dd>3. immediately; soon</dd><br>
<dd>시간이 얼마 지나지 않아 곧바로.</dd><br>
<dd>Before long; shortly</dd><br>
<dd>4. quickly</dd><br>
<dd>걸리는 시간이 짧게.</dd><br>
<dd>In the manner of taking a short time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>곧 [곧]</dt><br>
<dd>1. immediately</dd><br>
<dd>지체하지 않고 바로.</dd><br>
<dd>Quickly without delay.</dd><br>
<dd>2. soon; shortly</dd><br>
<dd>시간이 많이 흐르지 않고 머지않아.</dd><br>
<dd>Before long.</dd><br>
<dd>3. in other words; namely</dd><br>
<dd>바꾸어 말하면.</dd><br>
<dd>That is to say; put differently.</dd><br>
<dd>4. none other than</dd><br>
<dd>바로 다름 아닌.</dd><br>
<dd>Nothing less than.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>방금 [방금]</dt><br>
<dd>1. moment ago</dd><br>
<dd>말하고 있는 시점보다 바로 조금 전.</dd><br>
<dd>The moment before one speaks.</dd><br>
<dd>2. now</dd><br>
<dd>말하고 있는 시점과 같은 때.</dd><br>
<dd>The moment when one is speaking.</dd><br>
<dd>3. soon; shortly</dd><br>
<dd>말하고 있는 시점부터 바로 조금 후.</dd><br>
<dd>The moment after one has spoken.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>미구 [미ː구]</dt><br>
<dd>soon; shortly</dd><br>
<dd>얼마 오래지 않음. 또는 짧은 기간.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of not being long, or a short period of time.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>낼모레 [낼ː모레]</dt><br>
<dd>1. day after tomorrow</dd><br>
<dd>내일의 다음 날.</dd><br>
<dd>The day following tomorrow.</dd><br>
<dd>2. soon; shortly</dd><br>
<dd>가까운 미래.</dd><br>
<dd>The near future.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>내일모레 [내일모레]</dt><br>
<dd>1. day after tomorrow</dd><br>
<dd>내일의 다음 날.</dd><br>
<dd>The day following tomorrow.</dd><br>
<dd>2. soon; shortly</dd><br>
<dd>가까운 미래.</dd><br>
<dd>The near future.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>근간 [근ː간]</dt><br>
<dd>1. these days; nowadays; lately</dd><br>
<dd>얼마 전부터 이제까지의 매우 짧은 동안.</dd><br>
<dd>An extremely short period from a while ago to the present.</dd><br>
<dd>2. soon; shortly; coming</dd><br>
<dd>가까운 미래.</dd><br>
<dd>Near future.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>